# CONSULT-21 Independent Review

**Verdict:** The prior consensus is half-right and half-wrong. The ring *is* the failure surface, but **per-generation buffers were the wrong fix**. The real D3D11 gap is not Ã¢â‚¬Å“missing ring buffersÃ¢â‚¬Â Ã¢â‚¬â€ it is **(1) broken `ms_used` accounting that D3D9 does not have**, **(2) `CuiLayerRenderer`Ã¢â‚¬â„¢s lock-all-remaining pattern interacting with that accounting**, and **(3) D3D11Ã¢â‚¬â„¢s `Map(WRITE_NO_OVERWRITE)` lacking the implicit GPU fencing D3D9 `Lock` historically provided**. Frequent `WRITE_DISCARD` on one resource is protective because it triggers D3D11Ã¢â‚¬â„¢s **per-resource rename chain**; your per-generation build broke that contract and introduced a **deterministic lifetime bug**.

---

## 1. Resolving the D3D9 vs D3D11 contradiction

**The premise Ã¢â‚¬Å“D3D9 has the same ~370 discards/frameÃ¢â‚¬Â is false.** That discard storm is D3D11-specific, caused by accounting divergence.

### D3D9 (works): advance `ms_used` on unlock by actual count

