### `CuiLayerRenderer` turns that into ~370 discards/frame

```62:68:src/engine/client/library/clientUserInterface/src/shared/core/CuiLayerRenderer.cpp
	s_maxNumberOfVertices = s_vertexBuffer->getNumberOfLockableDynamicVertices(false);
	if (s_maxNumberOfVertices < 128)
		s_maxNumberOfVertices = s_vertexBuffer->getNumberOfLockableDynamicVertices(true);
	s_vertexBuffer->lock(s_maxNumberOfVertices);
```

On D3D11, one UI lock **instantly charges `ms_used` for the entire remaining ring** (~74k verts / 2 MB), writes a handful of quads, then unlocks without correcting `ms_used`. Every subsequent lock wraps Ã¢â€ â€™ `WRITE_DISCARD` cascade.

On D3D9, the same UI lock charges only the **actual** quad count on unlock Ã¢â€ â€™ ring stays mostly empty Ã¢â€ â€™ **~1 discard/frame** when the ring eventually fills.

So D3D9 is not Ã¢â‚¬Å“magically surviving the same hazard.Ã¢â‚¬Â It is running a **different, much healthier discard profile** because accounting is correct.

### What D3D9 `Lock(offset, length)` does that D3D11 `Map` does not

| Mechanism | D3D9 | D3D11 |
|---|---|---|
| Subrange lock | `Lock(ms_used, length, Ã¢â‚¬Â¦)` Ã¢â‚¬â€ explicit byte range | `Map(whole buffer)` + manual `pData + ms_used` |
| `NO_OVERWRITE` GPU contract | Runtime historically **blocked or fenced** conflicting locks | **No implicit sync** Ã¢â‚¬â€ caller must not overwrite GPU-in-flight regions |
| Per-frame reset | `beginFrame()` wired in `beginScene()` (`Direct3d9.cpp:2484-2486`) | `beginFrame()` exists (`Direct3d11_DynamicVertexBufferData.cpp:144`) but **zero callers**; `update_impl` is no-op (`Direct3d11.cpp:289`) |
| Default discard-at-frame-start | `false` on both (`ConfigDirect3d9.cpp:85`, `ConfigDirect3d11.cpp:53`) | same |

The bind/draw offset math is **not** the differentiator Ã¢â‚¬â€ both paths use stream byte offsets + `BaseVertexLocation=0`:

```3855:3858:src/engine/client/application/Direct3d9/src/win32/Direct3d9.cpp
