codex
One important repository fact: current D3D11 still maps the whole shared `ID3D11Buffer` and returns `mapped.pData + ms_used`; unlike D3D9 it does not pass an offset/length to the lock call itself. That does not automatically make it wrong, but it changes who is responsible for enforcing non-overlap: the D3D11 caller/ring must be exact.
